Eco by Naty wipes are made by natural, compostable and renewable material with 98,4% pure water. Since they are dermatologically and hypoallergenically tested (HRIPT test), Vegan, FSC certified and totally Chlorine Free, they don’t irritate the skin and are safe for use on sensitive skin. Certified for OK biodegradable WATER guarantee bio degradation in a natural freshwater environment, and thus substantially contribute to the reduction of waste in rivers, lakes or any natural fresh water. In response to our corporate mission, Naty has taken a great step and become one of the first wet wipes brands that is certified by TÜV Austria and Ecocert Cosmos. The greenest products available with award winning performance Ingredients #natywipes

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 1, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works well, but same SKU has different formulations and that can cause issues
reviews.reviewText: I have mixed feelings for this review. There are two products with the same SKU but different formulations. The UK formulation, that has the picture of the girl with the straw hat, is great. It provides more hygiene than I can achieve with dry toilet paper and I have no skin allergic reaction. The formulation made in Turkey with the the picture of the young girl with no hat in a red dress works well, but I have a skin allergy to the ingredients which are not the same as the UK version, even though the SKU is the same. I have also tried the Kirkland (Costco) flushable wipe brand and developed a significant skin allergy (it took about 8-months). My problem with Naty is that I make purchases based on the picture (the UK version), and since the SKU is the same, I often get the product I'm allergic to (the Turkish version). Bottom line, the product works great but, if you use it for an extended period of time and develop skin irritation problems, it is likely due to the product. I wish they would have distinct SKUs for the two formulations, since I would happily pay extra for the formulation that does not irritate my skin.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Just meh, at best.
reviews.reviewText: As someone else pointed out "Everything you don't want in a wipe". The wipes are awkwardly small, very fragile and easy to tear. They don't separate easily so you have to use two hands to peel them apart, which is tough when one hand is already contaminated or holding a baby. They also smell a bit weird, like faint chemicals. This is meh. Two stars because they are purportedly truly biodegradable, but who knows, eh?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works great, but smells funny.
reviews.reviewText: The one and only downside I have is that they smell odd. They are thick enough, big enough, and get the job done. They just smell odd. Not terrible, just not very pleasant. I may try adding a small amount of lavender essential oil if I can figure out how to do it without ruining the product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Thin and small.
reviews.reviewText: Very thin and small - about half the size of a normal Hugies or similar wipe. Need 2 just for normal use. I would not buy these again.

El anuncio que publicitan es engañoso. Te ofrecen un producto y te envían otro y sencillamente dicen que lo sienten, que has pagado solo por uno cuando claramente ponía que eran 12. Se dedican a retirar el anuncio sin más, pero eso es publicidad engañosa.

reviews.reviewTitle: Not the greatest wipe ive tried!!!
reviews.reviewText: Im not a huge fan of this brand of wipes. It does the trick when needed. But the wipes are hard to get out of the packaging and not very soft for the little ones!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 20, 2020
reviews.reviewText: Ok, maybe it’s just me being daft but I was expecting a much larger pack of wipes! The way the ad is worded is quite misleading in my opinion, £10 odd for one pack of 42 wipes is just astronomical! It’s such a shame that to be eco friendly you have to first have the luxury of a big fat wage packet!!! On top of that they just fall apart when you try and take them out of the pack. Definitely won’t buy them again!!
